						<div class="postbody">Doesn't the OS allow you to have it blit the entire window on the next frame without any tearing? It seems like very commonly-needed functionality, for anything showing any kind of video. At least on OS X (even back at 10.3, maybe earlier), this was automatic; once you were done with all the window drawing, I believe you just called a function to tell the OS to update it, and it would all occur on the next frame without any visual glitching or half-drawn things appearing.</div>

